and required for the installment of the solar plant in a lease for 25 years.\n\nAs offering the public land in a lease for the private sector is likely to cause many hurdles, the land lease agreement is made between NEA and CAAN.\n\nAsian Development Bank (ADB) is to finance the project through a private sector in this project.\n\nThe government is optimistic that the installation of solar panels will spread the positive message to the international community as well.","title":"10 MW solar plant to be set up at Gautam Buddha International Airport - Khabarhub","url":"http://english.khabarhub.com/2020/27/144822/","video":[]}
